head: cheesecake brownies
tail: preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) and grease a 9x13-inch pan

head: cheesecake brownies
tail: stir together the brownie mix, water, oil, and eggs until well blended

head: cheesecake brownies
tail: spread the brownie batter evenly into the prepared pan

head: cheesecake brownies
tail: beat together the cream cheese, egg, and sugar until smooth

head: cheesecake brownies
tail: dollop the cream cheese mixture on top of the brownie batter and swirl together using a knife or skewer

head: cheesecake brownies
tail: bake in the preheated oven for 22 to 25 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean

head: cheesecake brownies
tail: allow the brownies to cool in the pan, then cut into 24 squares and serve
